This paper deals with the fundamental limits of information and energy transmission in a multiple access channel, which involves information theory (cs.IT), networking and internet architecture (cs.NI), control systems (cs.SY), multimedia (cs.MM), and game theory (cs.GT). The paper also uses mathematical optimization techniques, which are common in many CS sub-categories. Therefore, cs.IT and cs.NI are the most likely sub-categories, followed by cs.SY, cs.MM, and cs.GT.
